1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:05,400
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:05,533 --> 00:00:06,767
Just when I was
finally correcting

3
00:00:06,900 --> 00:00:08,467
<i> all the wrongs I did to you,</i>

4
00:00:08,733 --> 00:00:10,300
<i>that was when you were
taken away from me.</i>

5
00:00:10,433 --> 00:00:12,167
<i> I love my dad.</i>

6
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:15,733
<i>He was the one
who always protected me.</i>

7
00:00:15,867 --> 00:00:17,033
<i> But...</i>

8
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:20,767
but I don't know what to do
now that he's gone.

9
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:23,433
[SOBBING]

10
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,633
<i>I wasn't even given a chance
to make things right.</i>

11
00:00:28,767 --> 00:00:30,933
Even just one day.

12
00:00:31,067 --> 00:00:33,367
<i>Mom has a charity event
in memory of Edward.</i>

13
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:35,567
Yes, this is perfect.

14
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:38,333
I now know how to execute
my final act of revenge

15
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:40,333
- against her.
- Mom! Marj?

16
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:43,600
I only know two people
who have a motive to do this.

17
00:00:43,733 --> 00:00:45,600
You should actually be
thanking us,

18
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:47,367
because you'll be reunited
with Edward now.

19
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,067
[GUN CLICKS]

20
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,333
[GUN FIRES]

21
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:53,967
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

22
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:59,300
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

23
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,100
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

24
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:23,300
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

25
00:01:36,567 --> 00:01:40,233
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

26
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:47,500
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

27
00:02:02,067 --> 00:02:05,867
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

28
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:11,200
Ash.

29
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:13,000
You should eat something.

30
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:15,400
You haven't eaten for two days.

31
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:17,533
And you've been missing
your medication too.

32
00:02:17,667 --> 00:02:19,000
She's right, Ash.

33
00:02:19,133 --> 00:02:20,833
You might get even sicker.

34
00:02:23,933 --> 00:02:26,833
What's the point of trying
to stay healthy,

35
00:02:26,967 --> 00:02:30,333
if my dad is no longer
in my life?

36
00:02:30,467 --> 00:02:32,533
Jasmine, all my life,

37
00:02:34,133 --> 00:02:37,233
dad was always on my side.

38
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:43,500
Every time I felt pressured
by mom about school,

39
00:02:43,633 --> 00:02:46,633
he would tell me that no matter
what my grades were,

40
00:02:46,767 --> 00:02:47,967
it's okay.

41
00:02:50,633 --> 00:02:54,133
As long as I was learning
and doing my best.

42
00:02:58,167 --> 00:03:02,433
And he supported me in wanting
to become a fashion designer.

43
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:08,167
He even hid all my drawings
from mom.

44
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:12,867
Because he knew,
she would just throw them away.

45
00:03:16,267 --> 00:03:18,133
I love my dad.

46
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:26,400
He was the one who always
protected me and defended me.

47
00:03:28,633 --> 00:03:29,733
But...

48
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:34,833
but I don't know what to do
now that he's gone.

49
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:37,400
[SOBBING]

50
00:03:41,067 --> 00:03:43,867
He's gone, Jasmine.

51
00:03:46,033 --> 00:03:47,133
Greg?

52
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:52,067
Ever since Edward's remains
arrived...

53
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:55,800
you haven't looked
at his casket.

54
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:01,233
Let's go to him and pray, okay?

55
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:09,433
Do I even have the right
to do that, Regina?

56
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,167
What?

57
00:04:17,867 --> 00:04:22,300
I'm not worthy to look at him.

58
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,933
All his life,

59
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:29,600
I only caused him
pain and suffering.

60
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:36,833
Just when I was correcting
the wrongs I did to him...

61
00:04:41,667 --> 00:04:43,767
he was taken away from me.

62
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:52,467
I wasn't even given a chance
to make things right.

63
00:04:56,467 --> 00:04:59,633
All he ever wanted
was your acknowledgement

64
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:01,300
and your affection.

65
00:05:05,067 --> 00:05:08,467
And when he passed away,
even for a short time...

66
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:12,533
you were able to give him that.

67
00:05:15,033 --> 00:05:18,367
So, you proved to him
that you could change.

68
00:05:19,667 --> 00:05:22,200
My dad!
[SOBBING]

69
00:05:24,167 --> 00:05:26,000
[SOBBING]

70
00:05:27,867 --> 00:05:29,133
Come on, Ash.

71
00:05:30,167 --> 00:05:31,300
You'll be fine.

72
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:35,167
Because you inherited
the strength

73
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:37,400
and kindness
of Uncle Edward.

74
00:05:39,433 --> 00:05:44,167
And for sure, he want you to use
those qualities to keep going.

75
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,900
Remember what my mom said?

76
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:51,200
We're always here for you.

77
00:05:53,367 --> 00:05:57,133
We may not be Uncle Edward,
but we're family.

78
00:05:57,267 --> 00:05:59,267
[SOBBING]

79
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,833
I'm still your sibling.

80
00:06:01,967 --> 00:06:03,633
Dad is still your dad too.

81
00:06:04,733 --> 00:06:08,733
We love you so much, Ash.

82
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:10,667
We all do.

83
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:13,633
[SOBBING]

84
00:06:17,667 --> 00:06:19,833
Jasmine.
[WAILS]

85
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:25,100
[WAILING]

86
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:38,400
Greg, Edward already
forgave you.

87
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:45,667
So, I think it's about time
you forgive yourself too.

88
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,867
Even just one more day.

89
00:06:52,633 --> 00:06:54,967
Even one more day.

90
00:07:00,567 --> 00:07:03,100
Just one day, Regina.

91
00:07:04,233 --> 00:07:07,967
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

92
00:07:09,167 --> 00:07:11,433
[SOBBING]

93
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:17,400
Even one more day.

94
00:07:22,133 --> 00:07:24,633
Just one day.

95
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:31,367
Just one day.

96
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:34,733
Even one more day.

97
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:38,667
Even one more day.

98
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:44,633
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

99
00:07:48,667 --> 00:07:51,267
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

100
00:08:03,967 --> 00:08:05,267
Love.

101
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:06,700
What are you doing?

102
00:08:08,533 --> 00:08:11,567
We Visayans have a belief.

103
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:16,033
With this chick,
every grain of rice it pecks,

104
00:08:16,167 --> 00:08:18,300
the one who killed Edward
will feel it.

105
00:08:20,533 --> 00:08:22,900
I hope they are never at peace
because of their conscience,

106
00:08:23,067 --> 00:08:24,867
Aldrin and Thea.

107
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:27,867
I hope they choke
on their guilt.

108
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,700
I hope they are haunted
every night.

109
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:33,033
[CHICK CHIRPING]

110
00:08:33,167 --> 00:08:34,700
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

111
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:36,133
I promise, Bro,

112
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:39,567
Marj and I won't stop,

113
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:42,333
until we find justice for you.

114
00:08:44,767 --> 00:08:48,233
We will make sure that
Thea and Aldrin pay

115
00:08:48,367 --> 00:08:49,800
for what they did.

116
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:52,767
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

117
00:09:01,667 --> 00:09:04,400
Are the police really doing
their job?

118
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:07,000
Edward has already been buried,

119
00:09:07,133 --> 00:09:08,867
and still nothing
is happening with the case!

120
00:09:11,367 --> 00:09:16,600
I'll double the reward money
to help with the search.

121
00:09:16,733 --> 00:09:18,233
So what? And then what?

122
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:21,100
We wait again for a witness
to come forward.

123
00:09:21,233 --> 00:09:23,133
This is torture, Greg!

124
00:09:23,267 --> 00:09:26,000
What? We just sit around
waiting, is that it?

125
00:09:26,133 --> 00:09:27,567
One day we'll wake up

126
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:30,067
and those criminals
already left the Philippines!

127
00:09:31,267 --> 00:09:33,833
Mom, please calm down.

128
00:09:33,967 --> 00:09:36,000
Dad and I are doing
the best we can

129
00:09:36,133 --> 00:09:39,067
to locate Thea
and Aldrin as well.

130
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,567
It is not enough!

131
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:48,700
It's all right.

132
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:51,167
- I'm sorry.
- It's all right.

133
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:53,567
- [GREG MUMBLES]
- I'm just frustrated

134
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:55,733
because the criminal
who did this to Edward

135
00:09:55,867 --> 00:09:58,267
is still roaming free.

136
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:02,400
I just feel that
I need to do something.

137
00:10:02,567 --> 00:10:03,600
It's all right.

138
00:10:03,733 --> 00:10:06,467
[SOBBING]

139
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:10,567
Mom, the only thing
we can do now

140
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:13,000
is to honor
the memory of Edward.

141
00:10:14,567 --> 00:10:17,033
Let's remember his goodness.

142
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:21,567
That's a brilliant idea, Marj.

143
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:26,167
We can honor him by helping
those who need...

144
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:29,400
a second life.

145
00:10:30,533 --> 00:10:33,200
Something that wasn't granted
to Edward.

146
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:38,067
What do you have in mind,
Grandmother?

147
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:42,600
I will establish a foundation
in Edward's name.

148
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:49,667
So that we can help those
who deserve a second chance

149
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,233
in their lives.

150
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:54,833
Those who went astray
but want to change,

151
00:10:54,967 --> 00:10:58,633
the victims of abuse
who want to start over.

152
00:10:58,767 --> 00:11:05,467
We can give them a new life
as a way of extending Edward's.

153
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:08,033
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

154
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:11,233
Dad will love that, Grandmother.

155
00:11:11,367 --> 00:11:12,433
He will.

156
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:18,700
That way, he will continue
to live in this world.

157
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,767
I want to help.

158
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:28,733
To make up as well for all
the bad things mom has done.

159
00:11:30,867 --> 00:11:32,333
I will help too.

160
00:11:33,667 --> 00:11:35,367
For Uncle Edward.

161
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:40,667
Then, let's plan everything
right away.

162
00:11:41,967 --> 00:11:45,700
Mom. I'm sure that Edward
will live on for a long time

163
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:47,800
because of this foundation.

164
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:51,200
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:12:03,633 --> 00:12:06,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

166
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:15,100
Aldrin, why haven't we left
the country yet?

167
00:12:15,267 --> 00:12:17,967
We already have passports
under different names.

168
00:12:18,100 --> 00:12:21,167
If we don't leave soon,
they'll find us here.

169
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:22,333
Relax!

170
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:27,433
I'm still looking for
an opportunity to kill Regina.

171
00:12:27,567 --> 00:12:29,667
Ever since Edward died...

172
00:12:30,933 --> 00:12:33,600
she's done nothing
but stay locked up in the house.

173
00:12:33,733 --> 00:12:35,633
And I can't attack them there

174
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:37,233
because their house
is heavily secured.

175
00:12:37,367 --> 00:12:38,633
[NOTIFICATION CHIMES]

176
00:12:44,933 --> 00:12:46,033
Look.

177
00:12:47,333 --> 00:12:50,467
Mom has a charity event
in memory of Edward.

178
00:12:50,633 --> 00:12:52,733
I think it's the perfect time
to strike.

179
00:12:59,867 --> 00:13:01,767
This is great.

180
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,767
Yes.

181
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:05,200
This is perfect.

182
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,433
I think I found my opportunity.

183
00:13:10,467 --> 00:13:11,533
I have an idea.

184
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:16,867
I know how I'll execute my final
act of revenge against her.

185
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:20,500
It's going to be one hell
of a blast.

186
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:23,533
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

187
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:31,167
Edward lived a tough life
while he was still alive.

188
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:36,200
He was a victim of the mistakes
of the people around him.

189
00:13:38,100 --> 00:13:39,667
I'm one of them.

190
00:13:41,133 --> 00:13:43,400
And I will forever be
remorseful.

191
00:13:44,933 --> 00:13:48,433
Sadly, just when he was
getting back up

192
00:13:48,567 --> 00:13:51,100
and starting a new life...

193
00:13:52,067 --> 00:13:54,767
he was taken away from us
so suddenly.

194
00:13:56,433 --> 00:14:00,100
That's why he'll never fulfill
his dreams.

195
00:14:00,233 --> 00:14:03,200
That's why we created
this foundation.

196
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:04,867
In Edward's name.

197
00:14:05,967 --> 00:14:09,067
We are creating a halfway home.

198
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:12,767
A safe space for those who want
to rebuild their lives.

199
00:14:14,267 --> 00:14:18,533
A place where they will not be
judged but guided.

200
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:20,700
Not abandoned.

201
00:14:21,733 --> 00:14:24,433
But given another chance.

202
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:31,667
Because every life deserves
the dignity of a second chance.

203
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:37,467
[APPLAUDING]

204
00:14:39,767 --> 00:14:42,767
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

205
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:48,267
[APPLAUDING]

206
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:58,300
Please accept this donation
from the Torrecampo family.

207
00:15:00,867 --> 00:15:07,167
[APPLAUDING]

208
00:15:12,733 --> 00:15:19,300
["KATOTOHANAN"
BY JESSICA VILLARUBIN PLAYING]

209
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:35,200
["KATOTOHANAN" THEME MUSIC
CONTINUES]

210
00:15:39,933 --> 00:15:41,767
Congratulations, Mr. Torrecampo.

211
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:43,233
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

212
00:15:43,367 --> 00:15:45,200
- Thank you.
- Thank you, thank you.

213
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:49,900
Mom handled that well,
didn't she, Dad?

214
00:15:50,033 --> 00:15:51,400
She did.

215
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:53,100
And I'm so proud of her.

216
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:58,233
Edward would have been
proud of her too.

217
00:16:00,267 --> 00:16:05,067
Do you think I fit
in the halfway house

218
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:06,700
your mom is building?

219
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:11,400
I'll be your roommate, Dad.

220
00:16:11,533 --> 00:16:17,600
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

221
00:16:19,567 --> 00:16:20,900
Daddy?

222
00:16:21,033 --> 00:16:22,067
Grandfather?

223
00:16:23,133 --> 00:16:24,500
- What's wrong, Jas?
- I've been knocking

224
00:16:24,633 --> 00:16:26,433
on mom and grandmother's door.

225
00:16:26,567 --> 00:16:27,867
Because mom has my medication,

226
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:30,800
but it seems like
they're not inside.

227
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:33,333
And I didn't see them
leave earlier,

228
00:16:33,467 --> 00:16:35,600
so they should still be inside.

229
00:16:35,733 --> 00:16:37,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

230
00:16:41,133 --> 00:16:43,833
Marj? Mom?
[KNOCKING]

231
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:44,933
Marj?

232
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:46,133
Mom?

233
00:16:46,267 --> 00:16:48,100
Open the door!

234
00:16:48,233 --> 00:16:49,467
Regina!

235
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:50,533
Marj!

236
00:16:50,667 --> 00:16:51,933
[KNOCKING]

237
00:16:52,067 --> 00:16:53,133
Mom!

238
00:16:54,667 --> 00:16:57,867
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

239
00:17:07,767 --> 00:17:10,633
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

240
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:21,433
Your mom isn't there.

241
00:17:21,667 --> 00:17:23,733
Neither is your grandmother.

242
00:17:23,867 --> 00:17:26,533
Oh, my god, where could they be?

243
00:17:26,667 --> 00:17:29,467
Could Aldrin Castelo
have sent another criminal,

244
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:30,567
just like before?

245
00:17:34,133 --> 00:17:36,000
Paolo, call security.

246
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:40,233
[PHONE KEYS CLICKING]

247
00:17:40,367 --> 00:17:41,433
Let's go.

248
00:17:45,833 --> 00:17:47,600
I'm the only one you need.

249
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:48,833
Let Marj go.

250
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,700
Please don't involve her.

251
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,467
Mom, no.

252
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,633
I won't leave you here.

253
00:17:54,767 --> 00:17:57,133
I won't allow you to get hurt.

254
00:17:59,067 --> 00:18:03,233
You're such a suck up,
as always!

255
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:06,400
Well then,
that hero complex of yours

256
00:18:06,533 --> 00:18:08,133
will get you killed.

257
00:18:08,267 --> 00:18:11,400
You don't have to do this.

258
00:18:11,533 --> 00:18:13,267
Let us go!

259
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:16,600
Why would we do that?

260
00:18:16,733 --> 00:18:18,200
[EXCLAIMS]

261
00:18:19,167 --> 00:18:23,067
After all the effort
sneaking into the event venue

262
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:24,767
just to abduct you?

263
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,333
You should be thankful to us,
actually...

264
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:33,167
because you'll be reunited
with Edward again.

265
00:18:35,867 --> 00:18:38,800
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

266
00:18:41,767 --> 00:18:43,433
What do you want? Money?

267
00:18:43,967 --> 00:18:44,800
Tell me how much.

268
00:18:44,933 --> 00:18:47,267
I'll call my spouse
and make sure you get

269
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:48,667
whatever amount
you're asking for.

270
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:50,500
I don't need your money!

271
00:18:50,633 --> 00:18:52,433
[LAUGHS]

272
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:55,967
I want you dead!

273
00:18:56,133 --> 00:18:59,367
What I want is for your family

274
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:03,300
to feel the pain I felt
when I lost my mother!

275
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:05,167
[SOBBING]

276
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:07,133
Thea, don't...

277
00:19:07,267 --> 00:19:11,400
Don't let him kill us.

278
00:19:11,533 --> 00:19:12,633
Please.
[SOBBING]

279
00:19:12,767 --> 00:19:14,900
Do you think
Ashley would be proud of you

280
00:19:15,033 --> 00:19:17,033
for what you're doing?

281
00:19:18,433 --> 00:19:20,667
Have mercy on your child.

282
00:19:22,033 --> 00:19:24,000
Please, don't do this.

283
00:19:24,133 --> 00:19:27,533
Don't use my child
to guilt trip me!

284
00:19:31,867 --> 00:19:35,033
I don't care anymore
what Ashley thinks.

285
00:19:36,867 --> 00:19:38,867
Even if she hates me for it.

286
00:19:40,233 --> 00:19:42,933
Besides, she prefers you anyway,
doesn't she?

287
00:19:43,067 --> 00:19:45,233
Fine, then be together!

288
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:49,700
I don't care about her anymore.

289
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:51,333
She's just a burden to me.

290
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:57,600
You're not just a criminal,
you're a murderer!

291
00:19:57,733 --> 00:19:59,600
And you're a worthless mother!

292
00:19:59,733 --> 00:20:03,800
Fine, you win!

293
00:20:03,967 --> 00:20:06,600
You're the good one
and the perfect one!

294
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:10,767
But I still have the upper hand
over you, Marj.

295
00:20:10,900 --> 00:20:14,667
Because I will walk out
of here alive.

296
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:18,333
And you,
this will be your grave.

297
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:21,100
What do you mean?

298
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:27,100
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

299
00:20:27,233 --> 00:20:28,633
We've reviewed
all the CCTV footage

300
00:20:28,767 --> 00:20:32,700
but it didn't capture
on the security cameras

301
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:38,400
who or how Mrs. Torrecampo
and Marj were taken.

302
00:20:38,567 --> 00:20:39,800
Wait, what are you saying?

303
00:20:40,867 --> 00:20:43,433
That someone tampered
with the security cameras?

304
00:20:43,567 --> 00:20:45,000
That all of this was planned?

305
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:47,600
It appears so, Sir.

306
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:51,500
I just buried a son
a few weeks ago.

307
00:20:52,533 --> 00:20:53,300
I will not allow myself

308
00:20:53,433 --> 00:20:55,500
to lose my spouse
and my in law too.

309
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:59,200
Dad, there are only
two people I know

310
00:20:59,333 --> 00:21:01,633
who have a motive to do this.

311
00:21:01,767 --> 00:21:03,233
Aldrin and Thea.

312
00:21:03,367 --> 00:21:05,067
I'm sure they're behind this.

313
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:10,200
Sergeant Molina,

314
00:21:10,367 --> 00:21:13,367
my family is only just starting
to rebuild again.

315
00:21:14,533 --> 00:21:16,967
Do everything to find them.

316
00:21:17,100 --> 00:21:19,133
I won't lose my family again.

317
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:22,233
Yes, Sir.

318
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:24,067
What are you planning, Aldrin?

319
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:27,233
What are you going to do to us?
Are you going to bury us here?

320
00:21:27,367 --> 00:21:30,633
[SOBBING]

321
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:33,867
[LAUGHS]

322
00:21:38,633 --> 00:21:40,467
Do you know what this is?

323
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:43,667
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

324
00:21:51,867 --> 00:21:54,233
I had to pull some strings
just to get this.

325
00:21:54,633 --> 00:21:58,367
Because I want you to die
with a bang!

326
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:01,600
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

327
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:10,867
<i>Sir Aldrin,
why are you still here?</i>

328
00:22:11,233 --> 00:22:12,367
<i>This place is already dangerous.</i>

329
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:15,833
<i>And besides, no one is allowed
inside the exclusion zone.</i>

330
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,033
<i> Relax.</i>

331
00:22:17,167 --> 00:22:20,800
<i>Your bosses sent me here, okay?</i>

332
00:22:20,933 --> 00:22:22,733
<i>I'm just making sure
nothing goes wrong</i>

333
00:22:22,867 --> 00:22:24,833
<i> with this demolition.</i>

334
00:22:25,900 --> 00:22:26,933
<i> Is everything cleared?</i>

335
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:29,033
<i> Sir, may I just ask something?</i>

336
00:22:29,167 --> 00:22:30,200
<i> Aren't I already fired...</i>

337
00:22:30,333 --> 00:22:33,100
<i>Can you just answer my question?</i>

338
00:22:33,233 --> 00:22:34,433
<i> Yes.</i>

339
00:22:34,567 --> 00:22:37,300
<i>Sir, the perimeter
is on lockdown.</i>

340
00:22:37,433 --> 00:22:40,033
<i>The guards are already
on the highway blocking traffic.</i>

341
00:22:40,167 --> 00:22:42,833
<i>I'm the only one left here
to trigger the switch.</i>

342
00:22:42,967 --> 00:22:45,667
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

343
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:50,267
<i>- Good.
- All right.</i>

344
00:22:52,633 --> 00:22:53,433
<i> [GUN FIRES]</i>

345
00:22:53,567 --> 00:22:56,100
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

346
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:03,867
Aldrin, please.

347
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,500
Please don't do this.

348
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:09,667
Like your mother,
I was betrayed too.

349
00:23:10,367 --> 00:23:14,467
But never would I want Jasmine
to take revenge on Thea.

350
00:23:15,667 --> 00:23:19,067
Because I don't want my child
to be consumed by pure hatred.

351
00:23:19,367 --> 00:23:21,000
If your mother were here,

352
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:24,267
I'm sure she'd want you
to forgive.

353
00:23:24,533 --> 00:23:26,433
She wouldn't like this.

354
00:23:26,567 --> 00:23:27,433
She wouldn't be happy.

355
00:23:27,567 --> 00:23:29,967
Aldrin, please, I beg you.

356
00:23:31,967 --> 00:23:33,300
Don't listen to him.

357
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,467
Don't worry, Dad.

358
00:23:36,767 --> 00:23:38,533
They are strong women.

359
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:40,500
And I'm sure they'll survive.

360
00:23:41,733 --> 00:23:44,133
Time is against us, Paolo.

361
00:23:44,267 --> 00:23:46,867
If we don't find them
right away,

362
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:49,433
who knows what those bastards
might do to them.

363
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:56,767
<i>Your location
is shared with her.</i>

364
00:23:56,933 --> 00:24:00,100
<i>Lalaine and I do that
when we travel abroad.</i>

365
00:24:00,233 --> 00:24:01,800
<i> So we don't lose each other.</i>

366
00:24:05,967 --> 00:24:06,900
That's it.

367
00:24:09,133 --> 00:24:10,133
What are you saying?

368
00:24:13,333 --> 00:24:16,133
I know now how to find
Marj and mom.

369
00:24:16,267 --> 00:24:17,600
[PHONE KEYS CLICKING]

370
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:20,033
Dad, they're at...

371
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:23,900
They're at our Asian Business
Complex project.

372
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:28,900
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

373
00:24:29,967 --> 00:24:32,700
In the building scheduled
for demolition today.

374
00:24:33,900 --> 00:24:36,333
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

375
00:24:40,567 --> 00:24:42,300
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

376
00:24:42,533 --> 00:24:43,533
Aldrin!

377
00:24:44,633 --> 00:24:45,733
What?

378
00:24:50,067 --> 00:24:51,500
You're right, Marj.

379
00:24:52,867 --> 00:24:55,533
My mother wouldn't be happy
with me...

380
00:24:57,500 --> 00:25:00,033
especially if I stop now.

381
00:25:00,167 --> 00:25:02,867
After planning all of this...

382
00:25:03,967 --> 00:25:05,667
for such a long time.

383
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:08,300
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

384
00:25:08,433 --> 00:25:11,767
[SOBBING]

385
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:14,467
You won't fool me!

386
00:25:15,733 --> 00:25:19,733
Don't waste your strength
begging!

387
00:25:21,133 --> 00:25:25,467
You'd better pray
with the time you have left!

388
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:28,767
Because when
this building collapses...

389
00:25:31,500 --> 00:25:33,200
you'll go down with it.

390
00:25:33,333 --> 00:25:36,700
[THUMPING]

391
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:42,333
[SOBBING]

392
00:25:42,467 --> 00:25:46,367
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

393
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:56,633
What could be happening
to mom and grandmother?

394
00:25:56,767 --> 00:25:59,167
I really hope they're okay.
I hope they get rescued soon.

395
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:02,467
Could mom be with the people
who took them?

396
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:05,567
Auntie Thea has been consumed
by anger and bitterness.

397
00:26:05,700 --> 00:26:07,767
I don't think you'll be able
to change her mind.

398
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:11,267
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

399
00:26:12,833 --> 00:26:14,533
Dad, please stay here.

400
00:26:14,667 --> 00:26:16,100
But I want to help.

401
00:26:16,233 --> 00:26:19,233
Dad, I promise you,
I will rescue mom and Marj.

402
00:26:19,367 --> 00:26:21,733
Just make sure, my child,
you bring them back to us.

403
00:26:23,433 --> 00:26:25,367
How will we escape the police?

404
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:27,200
- Do something!
- Be quiet!

405
00:26:27,333 --> 00:26:30,133
How can I think
if you keep talking nonstop?

406
00:26:30,267 --> 00:26:31,367
Put your guns down!

407
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:33,833
Surrender now if you don't want
to rot in jail!

408
00:26:33,967 --> 00:26:36,300
Even until death,
we will never surrender!

409
00:26:36,433 --> 00:26:37,333
[GUN FIRES]

410
00:26:37,467 --> 00:26:39,900
- [GUN FIRES]
- Whatever happens to me,

411
00:26:40,033 --> 00:26:41,300
promise me this, okay?

412
00:26:41,433 --> 00:26:44,133
Don't stop until Thea
is punished

413
00:26:44,300 --> 00:26:46,667
for killing Edward. Promise me!

414
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:49,300
Mom!

415
00:26:49,433 --> 00:26:50,767
I'll finish you!

416
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:52,367
You're next after your mother!

417
00:26:52,500 --> 00:26:54,100
I'll kill you!

418
00:26:54,233 --> 00:26:56,467
She's just like Edward!

419
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:58,333
She never truly loved me!

420
00:26:58,467 --> 00:27:00,167
She just ignored me!

421
00:27:00,300 --> 00:27:02,233
Be together in death!

422
00:27:06,133 --> 00:27:08,267
[LOUD EXPLOSION]
